  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>farfalle</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook<strong> </strong>for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>farfalle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580294863620-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580294863620-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580294863620-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580294863620-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580294863620-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pasta is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, squeeze your <strong>sausage meat</strong> from the skins into the pan (clean hands is the best way!) and discard the skins</p><p>Break the <strong>sausage meat </strong>up into bite-sized pieces with a wooden spoon and cook for 5-7 min or until crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580294873730-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580294873730-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580294873730-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580294873730-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580294873730-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[190ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580294878104-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580294878104-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580294878104-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580294878104-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580294878104-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is crispy, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and <strong>soft cheese</strong> and give everything a good mix up until combined – this is your <strong>creamy sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580294882098-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580294882098-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580294882098-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580294882098-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580294882098-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to the<strong> </strong>creamy sauce with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for a further 2 min or until the peas are almost tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580294886573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580294886573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580294886573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580294886573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580294886573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained farfalle</strong> to the <strong>creamy sauce</strong> with a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 1-2 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta – this is your <strong>creamy sausage & pea farfalle</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
